article.headline: Ohio 63, Navy 52
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. (AP) -- Jaivon Harris came off the bench to score a team-high 16 points and had seven rebounds as Ohio beat Navy 63-52 after 10 ties and 12 lead changes on Saturday night. The Bobcats (3-6) used a 22-9 run over the final eight minutes to defeat the Midshipmen (2-6) for the third straight year. Harris made 13 of his points in the second half, and Diamond Gladney added 12 points for Ohio. George O'Garro scored 17 points to lead Navy, and Laramie Mergerson added a career-best 14. But Jeff Charles and David Hooper, the team's leading scorers, were a combined 3-for-18 from the field and totaled nine points. Navy took its biggest lead at 39-34 on a 3-pointer from the left corner by O'Garro with 10:45 left, but the Mids hit just one field goal in the next 7:50. Jeff Halbert's 3-pointer with 6:26 left gave the Bobcats the lead for good, starting a 11-0 run. Halbert finished with seven points. Ohio led 23-22 at halftime, despite going nearly six minutes without scoring after taking a 9-6 lead.
